# {{mcpName}}

MCP server generated by [SLICE](https://github.com/) from the {{apiName}} OpenAPI spec (version {{apiVersion}}). Wraps {{tools.length}} endpoint(s) as MCP tools that any compatible agent can call.

## Installation

```bash
pnpm install
cp .env.example .env
# Fill in the secrets in .env
pnpm build
```

## Run

{{#ifEquals mode "local"}}
This server uses the **stdio** transport. Agents launch the binary directly.

```bash
pnpm start
```
{{/ifEquals}}
{{#ifEquals mode "http"}}
This server uses the **HTTP Streamable** transport. Agents connect over HTTP with a Bearer token.

```bash
pnpm start
# Listens on http://localhost:${MCP_HTTP_PORT:-8787}
```
{{/ifEquals}}
{{#ifEquals mode "both"}}
This server supports both **stdio** (for local agents like Claude Desktop) and **HTTP Streamable** (for cloud agents like n8n or Airia). Pick one at runtime via `MCP_TRANSPORT`.

```bash
MCP_TRANSPORT=stdio pnpm start    # default
MCP_TRANSPORT=http  pnpm start    # listens on http://localhost:${MCP_HTTP_PORT:-8787}
```
{{/ifEquals}}

## Connect to agents

{{#unless modeHttpOnly}}
### Claude Desktop (stdio)

Add this to `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json` (macOS) or `%APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json` (Windows):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{mcpName}}": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/absolute/path/to/{{mcpName}}/dist/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "UPSTREAM_BASE_URL": "{{baseUrl}}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
{{/unless}}
{{#unless modeLocalOnly}}

### n8n / Airia (HTTP)

Point the MCP node at `http://your-host:${MCP_HTTP_PORT:-8787}` and send `Authorization: Bearer ${MCP_SERVER_TOKEN}` on every request.
{{/unless}}

## Regenerate

Don't edit the generated files by hand. Re-run SLICE with the same spec and an updated selection to get a fresh bundle.
